A vintage 1960s travel poster style illustration of Singapore's urban landscape at dawn, showing a winding path that splits into three distinct routes across the island. In the foreground, a tiny figure stands at a crossroads in the north, while the routes snake through stylized HDB flats, lush tropical trees, and distinctive Singapore landmarks. One path follows an elevated train track past an airport with a curved modern roof, another weaves through multiple colorful MRT stations connected by dotted lines, and a third takes a direct diagonal route. The color palette features warm oranges, teals, and cream tones with a subtle paper texture. Birds dot the peachy morning sky above the iconic Singapore skyline visible in the distance.
